I"#<p><em>FCW</em> published a guest editorial we wrote on building a Federal Compliance Library to help streamline the authority to operate process.</p>

<p>From the post:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>When agencies can seamlessly tap into a communal resource to share and collaborate on commonly used components, they will have more time to focus on security postures that are truly unique and require more attention.</p>
</blockquote>

<blockquote>
  <p>By building a Federal Compliance Library based on open, iterative, collaborative principles, the federal government technology community will go further, faster.</p>
</blockquote>

